{
  "info": {
    "name": "NexServe Complete API",
    "description": "Complete Postman collection for testing all NexServe Backend APIs\n\nBase URL: {{baseUrl}}/api/v1\n\n## Setup\n1. Import this collection into Postman\n2. Set the following collection variables:\n   - `baseUrl`: http://localhost:5000\n   - `accessToken`: (will be set automatically after login)\n   - `refreshToken`: (will be set automatically after login)\n   - `userId`: ID of registered user\n   - `vendorId`: ID of registered vendor\n   - `bookingId`: ID of a booking\n   - `serviceId`: ID of a service\n   - `paymentId`: Razorpay payment ID\n   - `notificationId`: ID of a notification\n   - `reviewId`: ID of a review\n   - `invoiceId`: ID of an invoice\n\n## Automated Workflow\n1. Register a user → Login → Token auto-sets\n2. Register as vendor → Get vendor profile\n3. Create a service → Create a booking\n4. Update booking status → Create invoice\n5. Create payment → Send chat messages\n6. Leave a review → Check notifications\n",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "🔍 Health & Docs",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Health Check",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/health",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["health"]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Health check returns success', function() {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "    const jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData.success).to.eql(true);",
                  "});"
                ],
